SIMPLE: suffrage
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suffrage
<hw>Suf"frage</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>suffragium</ets>; perhaps originally, a broken piece, a potsherd,
used in voting, and fr. <ets>sub</ets> under + the root of
<ets>frangere</ets> to break. See <er>Break</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A vote given in deciding a controverted question, or in the choice
of a man for an office or trust; the formal expression of an opinion;
assent; vote.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I ask your voices and your <qex>suffrages</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Testimony; attestation; witness; approval.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lactantius and St. Austin confirm by their <qex>suffrage</qex> the
observation made by heathen writers.</q>
<rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Every miracle is the <qex>suffrage</qex> of Heaven to the truth of
a doctrine.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A short petition, as
those after the creed in matins and evensong.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A
prayer in general, as one offered for the faithful departed.</def>
<rj><au>Shipley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I firmly believe that there is a purgatory, and that the souls
therein detained are helped by the <qex>suffrages</qex> of the
faithful.</q> <rj><qau>Creed of Pope Pius IV.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Aid; assistance.</def> <mark>[A Latinism]</mark>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>The right to vote; franchise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suffrage</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Suffrage
<hw>Suf"frage</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To vote for; to elect.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suffragette</ent>⟦br⟧
